> Howdy, just figured I would share my problem and solution.
>   Issue, after playing my juke for a day, I noticed empty spots in the ma=
gazine.  Looking further I noticed some records we doubled up.  Some sets w=
ere completely in the wrong spot.  This has slowly getting worse and worse =
over the last few weeks.=20
> Solution.
>   After watching it run after just turning it on I noticed it left a reco=
rd.  What it appeared to do, when camming the gripper closed it would pick =
the arm up just a hair.  Sometimes this was enough to just miss the record.=
  Then play the next one on top and pick them both up.=20
>   What I did was disassemble the gripper arm by taking the gear screw off=
, and pounding the roll pin out.  Out came gripper, arm, cam, and both gear=
s.  A quick alcohol bath and cleaning with nylon brush and it was ready.  I=
 assembled it with Teflon silicone grease. =20
>   It now works like a charm.
